                         研究中心 首頁 > 學術研究 > 研究中心        量子科學研究中心  █ Material growth

Molecular beam epitaxy (MBE) and metal-organic chemical vapor deposition (MOCVD) for growth of wide band gap III-V/II-VI semiconductors and diluted magnetic semiconductors.
High-pressure reflection high energy electron diffraction (RHEED)-assisted pulsed laser deposition (PLD) for synthesis of self-assembled nanocomposites.
Chemical vapor deposition (CVD) for growth of nanomaterial heterostructures and 2D layer materials.

█ Device fabrications

Electron-beam lithography for patterning of novel nano-devices.
Inductively Coupled Plasma Reactive Ion Etcher (ICP-RIE) for dry etching.
E-beam and thermal evaporators for metal depositions.
Atomic layer deposition (ALD) and plasma enhanced CVD (PECVD) for dielectric coating.

█ Characterizations

Material characterization techniques: High-resolution transmission electron microscopes (HR-TEM), High-Resolution x-ray diffraction (HR-XRD), x-ray absorption spectroscopy (XAS), Raman spectroscopy, superconducting quantum interference device (SQUID), physical property measurement system (PPMS), etc.
Cs-corrected TEM for atomic-scale imaging of novel materials.
Optical spectroscopies: low-temperature photoluminescence (PL), micro-PL, magneto-PL, time-resolved PL, time-resolved pump-probe measurements, time-resolved Kerr rotation, cryogenic cathodoluminescence (CL) and scanning near field optical microscopy (SNOM).

█ Theoretical approaches

Density-functional theory for band structure and elastics properties of transition metal dichalcogenides.
Multi-band k.p calculations for electronic bands in semiconductor nanostructures.
Green’s function in the quantum scattering and the quantum transport.
Mean-field theory and non-equilibrium method including Keldysh Green’s function for transport of exciton-polariton superfluid.

             







